Planning
   - Define project scope and objectives.
   - Identify stakeholders and gather requirements.
   - Create a project plan with timelines and resources.
Requirement Analysis
   - Gather detailed functional and non-functional requirements.
   - Document use cases and user stories.
   - Conduct feasibility analysis.
Design
   - Create system architecture diagrams.
   - Design database schema and user interface.
   - Define APIs for client-server communication.
Implementation 
   - Set up the development environment.
   - Develop backend (APIs, database) and frontend (UI).
   - Integrate frontend with backend and implement core features.
Testing
   - Perform unit, integration, and system testing.
   - Conduct user acceptance testing (UAT).
   - Fix bugs identified during testing.
Deployment
   - Prepare and execute deployment plan.
   - Deploy to production and conduct smoke testing.
   - Monitor for post-deployment issues.
Maintenance
   - Monitor application performance and security.
   - Provide technical support and resolve issues.
   - Release updates, patches, and conduct regular backups.
Review and Evaluation
   - Gather feedback and conduct post-mortem analysis.
   - Document lessons learned and best practices.
  
